FBIS4-42817 "drweu111aa_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-111 Daily Report 8 Jun 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Bosnian Sides Accept One-Month Cease-Fire in Talks Bosnian Sides Accept One-Month Cease-Fire in Talks AU0806134594 Paris AFP in English 1329 GMT 8 Jun 94 AU0806134594 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Geneva, June 8 (AFP) -- Both parties to the Bosnian conflict, the Bosnian Serbs and the Moslem-Croat side, Wednesday [8 June] agreed to observe a month-long truce, officials said. Bosnian Serb leader Radovan Karadzic told reporters his side would observe the accord, which would be overseen by the United Nations Protection Force. Diplomatic sources said the Moslem-Croat federation had also signed the accord.
